Package komposten.leapjna.leapc.events

Class LEAP_CONFIG_RESPONSE_EVENT

java.lang.Object
com.sun.jna.Structure
komposten.leapjna.leapc.events.LEAP_CONFIG_RESPONSE_EVENT
All Implemented Interfaces:
LEAP_EVENT
@FieldOrder({"requestID","value"}) public class LEAP_CONFIG_RESPONSE_EVENT extends Structure implements LEAP_EVENT

Contains the response to a configuration value request.

Call LeapC.LeapRequestConfigValue(Pointer, String, LongByReference) to request a service config value. The value is fetched asynchronously since it requires a service transaction. LeapC.LeapPollConnection(Pointer, int, LEAP_CONNECTION_MESSAGE) returns this event structure when the request has been processed. Use the requestID value to correlate the response to the originating request.

Since:
LeapJna 1.0.0, Ultraleap Orion SDK 3.0.0
